Title : Gastrointestinal intraepithelial neoplasia
Text : 
{{technical|date=May 2014}}


'''Gastrointestinal intraepithelial neoplasia''' ('''GIN''' or '''GIIN'''), also known as "digestive epithelial dysplasia" is abnormal growth ([[cellular dysplasia]]) of digestive [[epithelial cell]]s in the digestive [[mucosa]].

Gastrointestinal intraepithelial neoplasia is the potentially [[premalignant]] transformation.

Since 2000, they are classified according to the Vienna classification.<ref>{{Cite journal
